# orinuno — Project Rules

## Stack

Java 21, Spring Boot 3.4.6 (WebFlux), MyBatis, MySQL 8.0, Liquibase, SpringDoc OpenAPI, Lombok, Testcontainers.

## Architecture

- `com.orinuno.controller` — REST controllers: Content, Parse, Export, Health
- `com.orinuno.service` — business logic: ParserService, ContentService, ExportDataService, KodikVideoDecoderService
- `com.orinuno.repository` — MyBatis mapper interfaces
- `com.orinuno.model` — JPA-like entities (KodikContent, KodikEpisodeVariant, KodikProxy)
- `com.orinuno.model.dto` — DTOs for API responses (ContentDto, ContentExportDto, etc.)
- `com.orinuno.mapper` — entity↔dto converters (ContentMapper, EntityFactory)
- `com.orinuno.client` — HTTP client to Kodik API
- `com.orinuno.configuration` — Spring configs, properties, filters
- SQL queries are in MyBatis XML files: `src/main/resources/com/orinuno/db/mapper/*.xml`
- Database migrations: `src/main/resources/com/orinuno/db/changelog/scripts/`

## Conventions

- This is an **open-source standalone** project. No imports from private projects (backend-master, kinodostup, etc.).
- No comments in code unless explaining non-obvious intent.
- Do not rename existing methods or fields without explicit request.
- Do not perform major refactoring unless explicitly asked.
- Kodik API domain is `kodik-api.com` (with hyphen). Never use `kodikapi.com`.
- Always use `COALESCE` when upserting `mp4_link` to avoid overwriting valid links with NULL.
- SQL parameters using `${...}` (string interpolation) must be validated via whitelist before passing to MyBatis.
- Use Lombok `@Data`, `@Builder`, `@RequiredArgsConstructor` consistently.
- DTOs are records where possible (`ContentExportDto`), entities are Lombok `@Data` classes.
- Tests use `WebTestClient.bindToController` for unit tests, Testcontainers for integration tests.

## Configuration

All config is under `orinuno.*` namespace in `application.yml`. Properties class: `OrinunoProperties`.
Security: optional API key via `orinuno.security.api-key`. CORS: `orinuno.cors.allowed-origins`.

## Git

- Never change git config.
- Never commit or push without explicit user permission.
- Never commit real API tokens or secrets (.env files are gitignored).
